cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the deployment of drone base stations for cellular communication, which involves network-based localization, coverage control, and collision avoidance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) as it deals with the deployment of drone base stations. Information Theory (cs.IT) is also relevant as the paper discusses UTDOA positioning. The paper also involves control systems (cs.SY) as it deals with coverage control and collision avoidance. Finally, the paper discusses security and cryptography (cs.CR) as it deals with the maximum number of severed users.
